inline_comments.message:
why don't insert the HazelCast cache (bean) in the class instead?!

After reviewing the remainder of this code I would just create a new class  like
TrustLevelManager wich wraps the cache and the notifications, not need to break it down in smaller user stories (its getting to small!)
The new class would have a reference to the cache and can use the notifation service. it WILL need a dedicate method to handle NEW Registration v. other (normal) TrustLevel Changes


pseudo code:

class TrustLevelManager

trustLevelPerCmHandle  (hazelcast map, injected)
notificationService    (injected)

static TrustLevel NO_OLD_VALUE = null


public initialTrustLevel(cmHandleId, trustLevel)

  if (trustLevelPerCmHandle.containsKey(cmHandleId) {
    // Ignore but log warning
  } else {
    trustLevelPerCmHandle.put(cmHandleId,trustLevel)  
    sendNotification(cmHandleId, trustLevel, NO_OLD_VALUE) 
  }

}

public updateTrustLevel(cmHandleId, newTrustLevel) {
  oldTrustLevel = trustLevelPerCmHandle.get(cmHandleId)  // Can be null, is OK
  trustLevelPerCmHandle.put(cmHandleId, newtrustLevel, oldTrustLevel )

}

private sendNotification(cmHandleId, newTrustLevel, oldTrustLevel) {
   create message
   if (oldTrustLevel != NO_OLD_VALUE) {
     Add optional message info about old value
   }
   notificationService.sendMessage()
}

